<h2>Redis CLI in Docker</h2>

<p>
    This will spin up an ubuntu container and install redis on it, you can then run CLI commands.
</p>

<pre>
    docker run --name red-ubuntu --network redis-bridge-network -i -t ubuntu
    apt-get update
    apt-get install iputils-ping
    ping google.com
    ping red-srv
    apt-get install redis-tools
</pre>

<h2>CLI Commands</h2>

<p>
    Redis command line interface.
</p>

<h3>SCAN, DEL</h3>

<pre>
    redis-cli -h red-srv --scan --pattern *:*:seed_sorted_set
    redis-cli -h red-srv --scan --pattern *:*:seed_sorted_set | xargs redis-cli -h red-srv del
</pre>

<h3>ZADD, ZSCORE</h3>

<pre>
    redis-cli -h red-srv ZADD myzset 1 "one"
    redis-cli -h red-srv ZSCORE myzset "one"
</pre>

